      "end": 5.72,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.54,
      "end": 11.18,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 12.06,
      "end": 15.54,
      "text": "Recorded by Pannie McCoy in Hudson, Colorado.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 16.62,
      "end": 19.76,
      "text": "Aesop's Pables, the Lion, the Mouse, and the Fox.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 20.72,
      "end": 28.06,
      "text": "A lion was lying asleep at the mouth of his den when a mouse ran over his back and tickled him",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 28.06,
      "end": 35.38,
      "text": "so that he woke up with his chart and began looking about everywhere to see what it was that had disturbed him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 36.0,
      "end": 41.86,
      "text": "A fox who was looking on thought he would have a joke at the expense of the lion, so he said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 42.32,
      "end": 45.92,
      "text": "Well, this is the first time I've seen a lion afraid of a mouse.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 46.78,
      "end": 50.76,
      "text": "Afraid of a mouse? Said the lion testily? Not I.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 51.46,
      "end": 53.68,
      "text": "It's his bad manners I can't stand.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 53.68,
      "end": 57.28,
      "text": "The lion, the mouse, and the fox.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
